   {
      "body" : "So your objection is that miners will spend their resources creating valid block headers for which they'll never get paid?\r\n\r\nRemember, the block isn't *confirmed* until the full block is received. I'm separating confirmation from propagation. It's the propagation time that's O(n) now and provides an incentive for miners to mine smaller blocks. Blocks would be *selected* based on propagation, and *accepted* based on confirmation.",
      "created_at" : "2014-08-11T20:30:22Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/4677#issuecomment-51836117",
      "id" : 51836117,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/4677",
      "updated_at" : "2014-08-11T20:30:22Z",
